abstract: More than 12,600 people in Iowa donated to Senator Bernie Sanders’s presidential campaign through the end of 2019.
snippet: More than 12,600 people in Iowa donated to Senator Bernie Sanders’s presidential campaign through the end of 2019.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — More than 12,600 people in Iowa donated to Senator Bernie Sanders’s presidential campaign through the end of 2019, giving him the largest number of donors in the state among the Democratic candidates, according to an analysis of fund-raising records filed with the Federal Election Commission.

abstract: The senators will return to Washington on Monday, taking them off the campaign trail in Iowa in the final hours before the caucuses.
snippet: The senators will return to Washington on Monday, taking them off the campaign trail in Iowa in the final hours before the caucuses.
lead_paragraph: INDIANOLA — Senators Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Amy Klobuchar will return to Washington on Monday for the Senate’s continuing impeachment trial of President Trump, taking them off the campaign trail in Iowa in the final hours before the caucuses.
headline_main: Warren, Sanders and Klobuchar will return to the Capitol on Iowa caucus day.

abstract: Caucusgoers, uniquely, will declare their loyalty before their friends and neighbors. And they are taking their responsibility very seriously.
snippet: Caucusgoers, uniquely, will declare their loyalty before their friends and neighbors. And they are taking their responsibility very seriously.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — It is a public display of civic duty unique in American politics: Iowans on Monday night will stand in front of their neighbors and express their preference for a candidate for president. No curtains covering a voting machine. No private paper ballots. Just a declaration of loyalty before fellow Democrats.

abstract: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state trying to fire up voters and make a last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
snippet: On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state trying to fire up voters and make a last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — On the eve of the Iowa caucuses, Democratic presidential candidates hustled across the state trying to fire up voters and make a last appeal to those struggling to make a final decision about their choice in the crowded field.
headline_main: In Iowa, Anxiety and Unpredictability Cloud Caucus Finish
headline_print_headline: In Iowa, Anxiety and Unpredictability Cloud Caucus Finish

abstract: Elizabeth Warren has had to skip taking photos with everyone who wants one at her events.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren has had to skip taking photos with everyone who wants one at her events.
lead_paragraph: INDIANOLA — It has become a symbol and signature of Senator Elizabeth Warren’s populist candidacy. She has called it a staple of democracy. But in these final frenetic days ahead of the Iowa caucuses, Ms. Warren is no longer staying for a personal picture with every single person who comes to her events and wants one.

abstract: President Donald Trump used a Super Bowl pregame interview to rail against Democrats, accusing them of hatred and offering schoolyard insults about his potential 2020 rivals.

headline_print_headline: Trump Bashes Democratic Rivals During Pre-Super Bowl Show

abstract: It’s the last full day of campaigning in Iowa, and we’ll bring you live updates from around the state.
snippet: It’s the last full day of campaigning in Iowa, and we’ll bring you live updates from around the state.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Welcome to the last full day of campaigning before the Iowa caucuses. We have reporters on the ground all over the state and will bring you live updates throughout the day.
